task.summary: Now ignoring c++ compiled shared objects
Fixed inverted axis when showing image
calc_denergy_at_turn() in longtrack cpp, timing executions of py and ftr
tomo_action __init__ now makes sure cpp lib is compiled
git now ignores .vscode, reconstruct_c imports os
changes to relative paths in reconstruct_cpp test

Namechanges, documentation and a small bugfix
- c1 is now dphi - written documentation for parameters and time space module - bugfix in calculating machine parameters when m.ref.frame > 1 - .so files are again ignored
Disabled assertions for self field parameter input
Re-added tests and assertions for bad input of space charge parameters
Added documentation and assertions for map info module
Moved assertion from reconstruct_c to map_info

Restructured main_testing and reconstruct_c
reconstruct_c.reconstruct() now takes the index of the profile to be reconstructed as input. In this way will it work in the same manner as tomography.run().
Added documentation to main testing.
Added documentation to the tomography class
reconstruct class now works in the same way as reconstruct_c
new_find_wf now works for one vector
Fast and functional new weight factor algorithm

Added and edited algorithms for calc wf and longtrack.
the class is now a mess.
Working algorithms: - longtrack_all - longtrack_one_particle - longtrack_one_particle_mod (spd-up with numba, ready for parallel) - wf_alg1 smooth, but hard to speed up - wf_alg2 super slow but intuitive - wf_alg3 faster version of alg2, may be used for reversed weights - compress_vector_njit (wf_alg4) currently best in speed (and intuition?)
some helping functions: - count - counts number of occurences of numbers in arrays. since there is no np.count. needed for speedup with numba - calc denergy - one of the more computing intensive parts of the longtrack funtion, speeded up with numba - find_accumulated_pixelvals another counting algorithm. creates large array

Particle tracking for each particle now running in parallel.
- Need testing. - Class need organising - New algorithms need testing - New tracking algorithm for one particle only runs in one direction
Added more timing, working on new method for calculating reversed weight

Working on 'new tomography algorithm'
- Running new tomography from main_testing - written function in reconstruction class for only tracking particles not also finding WF and such - Created new tomography class, currently running reconstructions of one test profile
